  "prompt": "What songs (of any genre) have the word \"Boogie\" in the title and/or in the lyrics?",
  "response": "Certainly! There are quite a few songs across various genres that have \"Boogie\" in the title or lyrics. Here are some notable ones:\n\n1. **\"Boogie Wonderland\"** by Earth, Wind & Fire featuring The Emotions\n2. **\"Boogie Oogie Oogie\"** by A Taste of Honey\n3. **\"Boogie Shoes\"** by KC and the Sunshine Band\n4. **\"Rock and Roll Boogie Woogie\"** by Bill Haley & His Comets\n5. **\"Jungle Boogie\"** by Kool & the Gang\n6. **\"Boogie Nights\"** by Heatwave\n7. **\"The Shoop Shoop Song (It's in His Kiss)\"** by Betty Everett (mentions \"boogie\" in the lyrics)\n8. **\"Boogie Woogie Bugle Boy\"** by The Andrews Sisters\n9. **\"Boogie With Stu\"** by Led Zeppelin\n10. **\"Boogie Woogie Choo Choo Train\"** by The Tractors\n\nThese songs span several decades and different styles, from funk to rock to swing. If you're interested in exploring more, you can look up each song to get a taste of the diverse ways \"Boogie\" has been incorporated into music.",
